HEADWORD: Protozoic
<hw>Pro`to*zo"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the Protozoa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Containing remains of the
earliest discovered life of the globe, which included mollusks, radiates
and protozoans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Protozoon</ent>⟦br⟧
